Class Sort

java.lang.Object
clinic.cs213project3.model.util.Sort
public class Sort extends Object
Class provides methods to sort lists in different ways. The primary sorting used is the Selection Sort algorithm. Sorting is used on the appointment lists for the clinic manager.
Author:
Aarush Desai, Rohan Vuppunuthula

  • Method Details

    • smallerThanMin

      private static boolean smallerThanMin(Appointment minApt, Appointment apt, String order)
      Method compares two appointment objects to find the minimum, given an ordering. Determines the order used to compare appointments in a selection sort.
      Parameters:
      minApt - The current minimum appointment in selection sort.
      apt - The appointment we are comparing with.
      order - String to determine what ordering method to use.
      Returns:
      True if apt comes before minApt, False if not or if "order" is an invalid string.

    • compareByPatient

      private static int compareByPatient(Appointment apt1, Appointment apt2)
      Compares two appointments by patient, date, and timeslot in that order. Used for the PP command.
      Parameters:
      apt1 - The first appointment.
      apt2 - The second appointment.
      Returns:
      -1 if apt1 comes before apt2, 1 if after, and 0 if the same.

    • compareByLocation

      private static int compareByLocation(Appointment apt1, Appointment apt2)
      Compares two appointments by county, date, and timeslot in that order. Used for the PL, PO, and PI commands.
      Parameters:
      apt1 - The first appointment.
      apt2 - The second appointment.
      Returns:
      -1 if apt1 comes before apt2, 1 if after, and 0 if the same.

    • compareByAppointment

      private static int compareByAppointment(Appointment apt1, Appointment apt2)
      Compares two appointments by date, timeslot, and provider's name in that order. Used for the PA command.
      Parameters:
      apt1 - The first appointment.
      apt2 - The second appointment.
      Returns:
      -1 if apt1 comes before apt2, 1 if after, and 0 if the same.

    • sort

      public static void sort(List<Appointment> appointments, String order)
      Performs selection sort on a list of appointments, given an ordering. The type of ordering on the appointments can be specified.
      Parameters:
      appointments - The list of appointments.
      order - The type of ordering to sort appointments by.

    • sort
